Here's a simple and informative README.md for your first website project:

Lucky Shrub Website

This repository contains the HTML, CSS, and (optional) JavaScript files for my first website: a simple, single-page website for Lucky Shrub, a local garden design and landscaping company.

Features:

    Clean and modern design: Utilizes Flexbox for responsive layout.
    Visually appealing: Incorporates subtle animations and hover effects.
    Mobile-friendly: Designed to be easily viewed on various screen sizes.
    Semantic HTML: Follows best practices for accessibility and search engine optimization.
    Includes:
        Home page with a promotional banner, service descriptions, and company information.
        Navigation menu with links to other potential pages (Services, Gallery, Contact).

Technologies Used:

    HTML: For structuring the content.
    CSS: For styling and layout.
    Flexbox: For creating a responsive and flexible layout.

Getting Started:

    Clone the repository:
    Bash

    git clone <repository_url>

    Open the project:
    Open the index.html file in your preferred web browser.

To Do:

    Create additional pages: Services, Gallery, Contact.
    Add more content: Detailed service descriptions, client testimonials, portfolio images.
    Improve accessibility: Add ARIA attributes and ensure proper keyboard navigation.
    Enhance responsiveness: Test and optimize for different screen sizes and devices.
